    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Material property and geometry sensitivity analysis for non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA",
    "description": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus was varied ±10% (from 110 GPa to 134 GPa) and screw outer diameter was perturbed ±0.05 mm around the nominal 7.5 mm; construct stiffness QoI varied by less than 4% across the full parameter space, and yield force QoI varied by less than 6%, confirming that the model predictions are robust to plausible manufacturing and material-property uncertainty. Friction coefficient at the screw-block interface was also swept from 0.1 to 0.4, producing less than 3% variation in the force at 40 mm displacement QoI."
  },
